page.title: 03Queensbury Landscape
page.content: The landscape around Queensbury can be described as half house and mills and half farmland. "Farmland" there's farms all over Queensbury they are small farms and they keep sheep, cows,chickens and other animals. Most of the farms have big feilds around it. "Mills" Theres few very big mills around Queensbury. Theres one mill what is over 100 years old its name is R.J Pachet they make locker's new buildings Ect. The others are down in the valley. "Village" The Queensbury village have alot of people and shops and pubs and take away's Ect. The transport is buses mostly there is alot of cars and there will be some taxi's round. Most of the people are old.
